---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { href } from '@/lib/i18n';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" lang="en">
  <article class="prose-page">
    <h1>About Medienrechtspraxis</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      Medienrechtspraxis is an open-access project providing daily-updated, AI-powered legal
      commentary on Swiss media law and personality rights.
    </p>

    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      Swiss media law is dynamic and practically relevant — yet current commentaries are
      often behind paywalls or outdated. Medienrechtspraxis fills this gap with freely
      accessible, structured legal analysis updated automatically on a daily basis.
    </p>

    <h2>Audiences</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Media professionals</strong> (journalists, editors, publishers) find plain-language
      summaries, checklists, and risk assessments in the Practice layer — no legal expertise required.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Lawyers</strong> (media attorneys, in-house counsel) use the Doctrine layer with
      academic analysis, marginal numbers, citations, and DACH comparative references.
    </p>

    <h2>Three Content Layers</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Practice:</strong> Accessible summaries with concrete guidance.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Doctrine:</strong> Academic commentary with marginal numbers, full citation
      apparatus, and comparative references to German and Austrian law.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Case Law:</strong> Current case law digest with thematic grouping,
      decision summaries, and significance ratings.
    </p>

    <h2>Open Access</h2>
    <p>
      All content is freely available under <strong>CC-BY-SA 4.0</strong>.
      The complete source code is on
      <a href="https://github.com/jonashertner/Medienrechtspraxis">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>MCP Server</h2>
    <p>
      In addition to the website, Medienrechtspraxis provides an MCP server (Model Context Protocol)
      enabling AI assistants to access the content programmatically, allowing LLMs to answer
      media law questions grounded in current, quality-checked legal analysis.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Medienrechtspraxis does <strong>not constitute legal advice</strong>. Content is AI-generated
      and automatically quality-checked. Professional legal counsel is essential for legal decisions.
      See <a href={href('/en/methodology')}>Methodology</a> for details on the generation process.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    max-width: var(--width-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .prose-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
  }

  .lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
